\subsection{Method \code{get_ticker()}}{
Get Ticker (Level 1 Market Data)

Retrieves real-time Level 1 ticker data for a symbol: the best bid/ask
prices, sizes, and the most recent trade price and size.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Request}: GET with \code{symbol} query parameter.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Single-row \code{data.table} with ticker fields.
\item \strong{Timestamp Conversion}: Coerces \code{time} (ms) to POSIXct in-place.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{GET https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/market/orderbook/level1}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/market-data/get-ticker}{KuCoin Get Ticker}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Spread Monitoring}: Calculate \code{best_ask - best_bid} for spread-based strategies.
\item \strong{Price Feeds}: Use as a lightweight price feed for mid-price calculation.
\item \strong{Execution Timing}: Monitor \code{sequence} to detect order book changes.
}
}

\subsection{curl}{

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{curl --location --request GET \\
  'https://api.kucoin.com/api/v1/market/orderbook/level1?symbol=BTC-USDT'
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

